The following Privacy Policy is written by Panini S.p.A. – headquartered in Modena, Italy, viale Emilio Po 380 – 41126, Tel. +39 059 382111 - Fax +39 059 827431 (hereinafter
“Panini”
)  as Data Controller for processing the personal data collected in, provided directly by you or however received or generated by us as a result of the use of the website Adrenalyn XL™ Calciatori 2024-2025 (
"Website"
or
"Websites"
) and the relevant applications for smartphones and tablets (referred to collectively as
"Application"
and/or
"Applications"
). Please note that this document has also been uploaded to third party platforms, the "Stores", or can be accessed via the latter.
Panini considers your privacy essential. We therefore ask you to read this information (hereinafter “Privacy Policy”) carefully in order to make a freely given, specific, informed and unambiguous choice when you are requested to give your personal data to Panini.
This Privacy Policy is divided into individual sections (
"Section" and/or "Sections"
), each of which deals with a specific topic so that you can read and search for them more quickly and easily. The Website and the App might contain links to other apps or websites. Panini is not liable for their privacy policies or for their content.
In general, all the personal data (
"Personal Data" and/or "Data"
) provided to Panini or collected during the use of Panini's services (collectively the
"Services"
and/or individually the
"Service"
, as better defined in Purpose No. 1 entitled Provision of Services in Section –
“B. Purposes of Personal Data Processing”
of this Privacy Policy, will be processed lawfully and in a transparent manner in accordance with the principles stated in the current legislation on the protection of personal data, such as transparency, fairness, lawfulness, data minimization, purpose limitation, accuracy, storage limitation, integrity and confidentiality.
This Privacy Policy is written on the basis of the transparency principle using simple language to increase the level of understanding of the statements given.
A- Type of Personal Data Processed
Personal Data collected are listed below.
Game user data
Accessing the mobile Application you can decide to use the Application as guest users or create a registered user account. Accessing the application by website an Account is required.
Both for guest users and registered users, Panini will collect statistical information about the game usage such as digital collected cards (including detailed information about date-time the digital cards have been received, IP address during the matches), code activations, user ID, username generated randomly by the system, emblem configuration, granted rewards, country of residence, access portal, mobile device app ID (i.e. for push notification) and technical information about the user device to ensure the functioning of the game and identify if the device is an iOS or an Android device.
This information will be associated with an internal user ID that cannot be directly traced back to a person.
For guest users, this information is not associated with any personal identity unless users choose to convert guest user status to a registered user account. In this case, the game user data collected so far will be associated with the user account created and therefore with a personal identity.
Name, Last name, Contact Details and other Personal Data
When you create an account into the Website or through the Application.  Panini may ask your personal information such as: email, name, last name, gender,username, contact details, month and year of birth, soccer team supported and country of residence. In the same way, you may be asked to indicate other Data such as data coming from your submission of texts, drawings or registration information, on the occasion of participation in competitions, promotions, interactive games (such as those belonging to the Adrenalyn category) and initiatives of any kind.  Further Personal Data may be collected during the management of every relationship with Panini or it may consist of the data you decide to provide Panini via Customer Service (also accessible by telephone), or your use of the Contact area accessible through the Website or the Application.
Some sections of the Website or Application and the nature of the communications you freely decide to send us via the electronic or physical addresses on the Website or App envisage empty text boxes, in which you can give Panini information, which may contain Personal Data. Being free fields, you may choose to communicate (even inadvertently) particular categories of Personal Data, such as those revealing political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or union membership, as well as genetic data, biomedical data which can permit to uniquely identify a specific person, data related to health or sex life or sexual orientation.
Panini asks you not to reveal any of these types of Data, unless you believe it strictly necessary so that we may follow up the request sent to us. Since, as mentioned, the provision of such information is entirely optional, should you decide to do so, Panini may only process said information with your explicit consent and in compliance with current regulations. Accordingly, Panini stresses the importance of granting your explicit consent for the processing of those special categories of Personal Data, should you decide to share that information with Panini.
Personal Data of Third Parties
As mentioned in the previous paragraph, free text fields in either the Application or Website make it possible to create any type of message, including those that contain Personal Data relating also to other people. In all cases in which you decide to share such Data, you will be considered a self-appointed Data Controller and, as such, you will have to assume all the relevant legal obligations and responsibilities. Therefore, in this regard, you undertake to hold Panini harmless from any dispute, claim, request for compensation for damage from data treatment etc. that could reach Panini from people whose Personal Data have been forwarded by you in violation of the applicable rules on the protection of Personal Data.
If you are below 18 years of age (“Minor” and/or “Minors”) and want direct access to section of the Website and/or App reserved for registered users, you must provide Data regarding your parent or guardian so that person can accept on your behalf the General Conditions of Use of this Service.
If you are below 16 years of age or, under local laws, below the age allowed for the processing of Personal Data based on consent and, in all cases, below 14 years of age (“Privacy Minor” and/or “Privacy Minors”) and want direct access to the sections of the Website and/or App reserved for registered users, you must provide Data regarding your parent or guardian so that person can accept on our behalf the General Condition of User of this Service and will be also asked to read and declare to have understood the current Privacy Policy before validating your request with the Website or App.
In order to process that Data and create the
“Register of Parents/Guardians”
, Panini will apply the specific "
Privacy Policy for parents or guardians of Adrenalyn users
" found at the foot of this page.
Data processed during interaction with social networks
You can also access the on-line game Adrenalyn XL™ by using your personal account on one of the social networks included on the registration form. In this case, the social network will automatically send Panini your Personal Data. You will only have to provide the additional Data required to complete your registration, which has not been provided by the social network,. To know which Data the social network will share with Panini, please read the Privacy Policy provided by the social network you access and refer to the options for sharing Data indicated therein. Additionally, please note that in such cases Panini will provide specific privacy information, the latest version of which is always available
by clicking here
.
IP address spatial coordinates
When you create a profile on the Website or through the Application, we will collect the approximate spatial coordinates (state, city) of your IP address associated, only, with your last log-in. We will keep this information only to the extent strictly necessary and proportionate to ensure the purpose of Security, therefore for the sole purpose of obtaining information necessary to identify anomalies, fraudulent activities and/or abuse in the use and access to the Website and the Application.
Navigation Data and Cookies
(applicable when you use the Website)
The computer systems and software used to run the Website acquire, during their normal operation, some Personal Data whose transmission is implicit in the use of Internet communication protocols. This information is not collected by Panini to be associated with identified data subjects, but by its very nature could, through processing and association with data held by third parties, allow data subjects to be identified. This category of data includes the IP addresses or domain names of the computers used by the users connecting to the Application, the addresses in URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) notation of the requested services, the time of the request, the method used in submitting the request to the server, the size of the file obtained in response, the numerical code indicating the status of the response given by the server (good result, error, etc.) and other parameters related to the operating system and the user's computer.
These data are used for the sole purpose of obtaining anonymous statistical information on the use of the Website, to check its correct functioning and to identify anomalies and/or abuses. Except in cases where the data are used to ascertain responsibility in the event of hypothetical computer crimes against the Website or third parties, these data do not persist for more than seven days.
Information about the use of cookies is available in our Cookie Policy, which we kindly ask you to read by clicking on the “Manage cookies” button or the
both available in the Website footer.
Data of your Device (applicable when you use the App)
By selecting the option "Install" in the App Store, you authorise Panini to access certain Personal Data and other information on your mobile device ("Device"), which is essential for a successful installation (e.g. Device model, version of the operating system, screen resolution, type of network connection, language, etc.)  Sharing this information is essential to install the App and you can stop it by removing the App from your Device.
SDK and tracking technologies (applicable when you use the App)
SDK (Software Development Kit) and similar technologies are information the mobile apps record and/or read on your Device. These technologies usually enable the use of a mobile app to be analysed in order to avoid malfunctions and improve user experience.
Via the App, Panini uses SKD and similar technologies supplied by third parties, depending on the circumstances, as autonomous data controllers compared to Panini (using the Data they collect for their own purposes and according to the terms and conditions they have established) or as Data Processors (using the Personal Data on behalf of Panini).
