B- Purposes of the Personal Data Processing
We will process your Personal Data for the following purposes:
to allow operations strictly connected and contributory to the management of our relations with you, such as respond to queries received via the contact forms or by Panini (electronically and/or in printed form) at any of the addresses specified on the Website or the App; allow you to access private sections of the Website or App; help if you forget your personal account login/password for the Website or App; allow you to take part in interactive games, initiatives, prize competitions and events; send you push notifications about the App; send you (if you are a Minor and your parent/guardian previously granted consent on your behalf for processing linked to the supply of services by the information provider, such as for registration with the Website or the App, or for Marketing and Profiling purposes) a communication informing you, when you reach the minimum age established by law, that you can manage your personal data independently and grant consent for processing linked to the supply of services by the information provider with full autonomy; send you communications about the upcoming deactivation and deletion of your account
(Provision of services)
;
to allow us to fulfill obligations established by laws, regulations and community legislation (e.g. collect Data required to verify parental responsibility for the Minor), or instructions given by authorities empowered by law or by supervisory and control bodies, and to allow us to fulfill our accounting and tax obligations
(Legal obligations)
;
to get the information required to identify anomalies, illegal activity and/or abuse of the use of the Websites and App towards Panini or third parties
(Security)
;
sending you, if you are using or have used a Panini Service or if you are buying or you have bought a product or a service through the Website, direct marketing and promotional communication via e-mail about similar products or services
(Soft Spam)
;
to provide information on our products and/or services, including promotional and commercial activities, market research and marketing or, activities to measure the level of customer satisfaction by sending questionnaires, carrying out surveys or opinion polls. The activity may be carried out by using automated systems without an operator (e.g. e-mail), but also via traditional contact methods (e.g. postal services and telephone) and via the App push notifications with marketing contents, if you use the App
(Marketing
);
to set up user groups by processing the data they have provided, by using the third party profiling cookies - if you accept them - on the Website, by collecting and analyzing the information on the preferences selected and choices made via the Website or the App - if you use it - and via your Device data, so as not to indiscriminately send generalized, commercial and promotional communications to all users and to customize the Services provided via the App, if you use it. This enables us to segment users into groups organized in way that reflects their interests, such as country of origin, language, gender, previous purchases etc. As a consequence, we can send commercial communications - using automated systems without operator action (e.g. e-mail), as well as via traditional contact methods such as the postal service and the telephone, or via App push notifications, if used by you - that are as relevant and least invasive as possible, limiting to the extent possible the situations in which you receive messages that are not of interest to you
(Profiling)
;
to provide, for specific initiatives, the contact Data supplied to create an account or profile on the Website, or obtained via the App, to third parties - individually and specifically indicated each time in the related consent form, when present at the time the Data is supplied - with which Panini has commercial relationships, so that they can send you promotional/marketing communications and commercial information, or carry out market research with regard to their products and services
(Communication to third parties)
.
C- Processing of the Personal Data of minors under the minimum age established by law for consent-based processing of Personal Data
Children aged less than 16 years old or, in accordance with national local laws, below the age set to directly collect the consent to the processing from children but in any case not less than 13 years old (hereinafter "Privacy Minor" or "Privacy Minors"), require the consent of one of their parents or legal guardians to register on the Website or Application to access the sections reserved for registered users.
Since Panini is a company based in Italy, 14 is the minimum age for collecting consent (without this having to be given by a parent or guardian) to process your Personal Data for purposes linked to the Provision of Services (including such company services as registration with the Website and App and access to their respective private sections), the conduct of marketing campaigns, profiling based on the collection of browsing and purchasing data, and the communication of user data to third parties. If, however, the local laws of the EU country in which the Privacy Minor resides establish a higher age threshold for giving consent for processing, the latter will prevail.
Privacy Minors of Age workflow registration is as follows:
The Privacy Minor must filling the registration form on the Website or Application giving all the personal data requested together with the name, surname, degree of kinship, email address of a parent or legal guardian of his.
Registration of the Privacy Minor is on hold until his parent or legal guardian manages the request of the registration. To be able to do this, the parent of the legal guardian must create an account on Panini Parents/Legal Guardians Register by following the link included in the email received by
noreply@paninigroup.com
.
In case the parent or the legal guardian don't use the link within 72 hours from the reception or doesn't give consent to the processing of the personal data requested in the registration form, Privacy Minor will not able to access the sections of the Website or Applications under registration and the data collected in the registration form will be canceled in 24 hours.
After creating an account, the parent or guardian may examine and correct the Data sent by the Privacy Minor, as well as give and manage the consents required to process the Personal Data of the Privacy Minor needed to register with the Website and App and access the respective private sections. In order to take concrete steps to protect the Personal Data of Privacy Minors, Panini does not process any such Data for marketing or profiling purposes, or for communication to third parties.
If the parent or guardian approves the registration request, the Privacy Minor can then access the Websites and Apps at any time, without further notifications to the parent or guardian. The parent or guardian may also be notified about the consent requested to process the Data of the Privacy Minor needed for access to versions of the Websites and Apps dedicated to Adrenalyn Online that require additional processing with respect to previously-authorized versions of them (e.g. for participation in prize competitions).
The Privacy Minor will not able to change the personal data included in the registration form and only the parent or legal guardian are allowed to do it by entering the Panini Parents/Legal Guardians Register or by contacting Panini at the address
webprivacy@panini.it
On the first day of the month in which the Privacy Minor reaches the age established by law for giving independent consent for the processing of his/her Personal Data, Panini will send a communication to the parent or guardian stating that, from the start of the month following receipt of the e-mail, the consents given by the parent or guardian on behalf of the Privacy Minor will no longer be valid and, from the first login to a Panini Service after that date, the last mentioned will be invited to give consent for the processing of his/her Personal Data for marketing and profiling purposes and (in relation to certain initiatives) for communication to third parties (which, as mentioned, Panini does not do in relation to Privacy Minor Data Subjects). An e-mail describing this procedure will also be sent to the Privacy Minor.
Accordingly, on reaching the minimum age envisaged by law, the Privacy Minor may give direct consent for the processing of his/her Personal Data, having become fully autonomous in the management of such Data and the related rights recognized in the applicable legislation, as well as in the expression of his/her preferences and consents. The parent or guardian will therefore cease to manage the Personal Data of the Privacy Minor.
Users minor of 18 are not allowed to purchase goods or services from our Website and Application. To complete the registration process, under 18 years of age users also need the acceptance of the General Conditions of Use by the parent or guardian as described in the General Condition of Use this service.
D- Lawful Basis for Processing Personal Data, Mandatory/Discretionary Provision of Personal Data and Consequences in case of not providing
The lawful basis for processing your Personal Data by Panini, in accordance to the purposes in Section
"B- Purposes for processing Personal Data
, of this Privacy Policy, is as follows:
The provision of Personal Data and the relevant processing for Services Provision & Contractual Obligations.
if you are not a Privacy Minor:
is strictly to execute the service requested and to correctly implement the contractual relationship in place with you, directly or through the acceptance of your parent or guardian in case you are under 18 years of age,  and, therefore, this constitutes an essential condition to enter into a contractual relationship and is also the legal basis for the processing. As a result, if you fail to provide the Personal Data requested, or give incorrect data, Panini will be unable to implement the service and fulfil the contractual relationship and will have the legal right to refuse to implement or to interrupt the implementation of the service
if you are a Privacy Minor:
the provision of services by the information provider, e.g. registration with the Website and/or App, is based on the consent given directly by your parent or legal guardian (according to the
preceding Section C
).
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing for purposes related to
Legal Compliance
, is necessary for Panini in order to comply with the related legal obligations. When you provide your Personal Data to Panini, we must process them in accordance with applicable laws which may include the storage and communication to the competent authorities for compliance with tax, customs or other obligations.
The provision of Personal Data, and the related processing, for the purposes related to the activity of
Soft Spam
is based on the legitimate interest of Panini to send marketing communications via e-mail regarding products and services similar to those you have already used or purchased. You can stop receiving these communications without any consequence (except you will be unable to receive any further communications of this type from Panini), by using the link (the "Cancel" key) placed at the bottom of each e-mail received for that purpose.
The provision of Personal Data and their processing for purposes related to
Security
are based on (i) the interest of Panini to identify and prevent any illegal behaviour and to determine the responsibilities in the event of computer crimes to the detriment of the Website or Application such as to compromise the availability, authenticity, integrity and confidentiality of the Personal Data stored or transmitted, which, consequently, (ii) on yours in order to detect and follow up the appropriate checks in case of fraudulent access or acts illegal through the profile you created on the Website or through the Application.
The provision of Personal Data and its processing for
marketing
purposes is based on the collection of your explicit consent, which may be given via a specific checkbox and/or the cookie banner displayed on the Website. You are under no obligation to give that consent to Panini and, if you do, you are free to revoke it at any time without any consequences (except that you will no longer receive marketing communications from Panini). You can revoke the consent given for that purpose by following the instructions in Section
H-Data Subjects Rights
section of this Privacy Policy.
The provision of Personal Data and its processing for
profiling
purposes is based on the collection of your explicit consent, which may be given via a specific checkbox and/or the cookie banner displayed on the Website. You are under no obligation to give that consent to Panini and, if you do, you are free to revoke it at any time without any consequences (except that you will no longer benefit from the customization of commercial offers from Panini or, if applicable, your experience using the App). Similarly, browsing on the Website and taking advantage of the various functions will not be compromised in any way, nor will you suffer any adverse consequences. You can revoke the consent given for that purpose by following the instructions in Section
H-Data Subjects Rights
section of this Privacy Policy.
We will use a specific checkbox to collect your explicit consent to provide and permit the relevant processing of your Personal Data for
Communication
purposes to third parties. You are under no obligation to provide Panini with your consent and, if you do so, you are free to withdraw it at any time. The only consequence will be to prevent communication of your personal data to any third parties, specifically named individually from time to time in the relevant consent form when you provide your Data, so they may subsequently send you marketing communications. We wish to specify that this particular consent form is provided and is present only when specific initiatives are running. You can withdraw your consent to the communication of your Data by following the instructions in Section "
H- Your Rights as Data Subject
" in this Privacy Policy.
E- Personal Data Sharing
The Personal Data will be made known to the Panini staff in charge of the development and management of the Website or the Application that is authorized to process them for the purpose of achieving the aforementioned purposes and who are committed to confidentiality or otherwise have received an appropriate legal obligation to confidentiality.
Personal Data may be shared, used and transferred within the companies belonging to the Panini group for accounting and administrative purposes.
Personal Data will be made known to third parties, appointed as Data Processors, as they process Data on behalf of Panini (for example, suppliers with whom it is necessary to interact for the
Service Provision
such as hosting providers, platform providers for sending e-mails or, again, suppliers who perform technical maintenance activities including the maintenance of network equipment and electronic communications networks, suppliers who develop interactive games and competitions).
Personal Data may be shared with third parties with whom Panini has ongoing contractual relationships concerning services functional to the performance of the activity (such as couriers for the delivery of products, audit firms, persons, companies or professional firms that provide assistance and advice on the subject, administrative, legal, tax, financial and credit recovery firms relating to the provision of the Services).
The contact data you give to create an account or profile on the Websites or via the App may be communicated to third parties - individually and specifically indicated each time in the relevant consent form, when present at the time the Data is provided - only if you give your explicit consent via a specific tick box.
Finally, Personal Data will be communicated when requested to the competent taxation offices, or to other public bodies, according to the provisions of the laws in force.
Personal Data is not intended for publication or dissemination.
F- Personal Data Transfer
Given the international presence of Panini, some of your Personal Data may be shared with recipients, described in the previous section, located in countries that are not members of the European Economic Area. Such Data transfers will be the subject of adequate guarantees, including adequacy decisions and Standard Contract Clauses approved by the European Commission, in combination with the adoption of additional legal, technical and organizational measures or other guarantees intended to protect the Personal Data adequately, in accordance with the related European regulations.
More information is available by writing to Panini at the following address:
webprivacy@panini.it
G- Personal Data Retention
The Personal Data processed for the
Provision of Services
will be retained by Panini for the period strictly needed to provide the requested service and execute properly the contractual relationship with you. In all cases, since such Personal Data is processed in order to provide Services to you and execute the contractual relationship, Panini may retain it for a longer period, especially when and to the extent necessary to protect its interests from any liabilities that may arise in relation to the Services.
In all cases, Panini confirms that the retention time for games data, and any orders and purchases made, is 12 months from the date on which the Website is removed from the Internet and the App is removed from the Apple Store and Google Play. At the end of such period, any Data that enables a natural person to be identified (even indirectly) will be rendered anonymous and retained solely in aggregated form for statistical purposes. Panini will maintain the validity of your authentication credentials for access to the Website and App Services for a period of 54 months from your last access (the centralized registration system for Websites and the App used by Panini is common to all e-commerce websites and, therefore, all authentication credentials have the same validity period. Such retention period reflects the frequency of major sporting events, such as the Football World Cup, and the purchasing behavior of our website users). Before that period expires, Panini will send a communication about the upcoming deletion of your account to the contact addresses provided by you. At the end of the retention period, the Data will be deleted or anonymized.
Your requests, and the data contained in them, collected via the Customer Service or Contact area reachable through the Website and the Application will be maintained for one year from the closure of the request in order to allow Panini to handle any additional requests received after closure. At the end of this period the Data that permit the identification, even indirect, of a physical person (such as name, surname, e-mail) will be made anonymous and maintained, only in the form of aggregated data, for statistical purposes.
The Personal Data processed for the purposes of
Legal Compliance
will be retained by Panini for the period envisaged by specific legal obligations or applicable legislation.
Personal Data processed for the purposes of
Security
-will be kept by Panini for the time strictly necessary for the said purposes, namely until the moment when Panini will be required to keep them in the event of legal recourse to transmit these Data to the competent authorities.
Panini will retain the Personal Data processed for Marketing and Profiling purposes until you revoke your consent. Once consent is revoked, Panini will cease to use your Personal Data for those purposes, but may continue to retain it to the extent necessary to protect its interests from any liabilities that may arise from such processing (for example, some of your identification Data may be retained so that Panini can demonstrate that, at any given time, your consent was acquired and/or revoked properly).
In compliance with the limited retention principle, any consents given for marketing purposes will be maintained for a maximum of 54 months from the last access/login. As described above, this is consistent with the logic applied for the retention of authentication credentials giving access to the Services (since the prolonged inactivity of your account will indicate to Panini that you are no longer interested in our products).
Storage times of Personal Data processed for
Communication to third parties
are the same as those indicated above for authentication credentials. The reason behind this is that the information provided, following specific consent, consists only of the contact data provided when you created an account or profile on the Websites or via the App. Nevertheless, it remains understood that if you revoke your consent, Panini will stop communicating that Data to third parties individually and specifically indicated in the relevant consent form.
H- Data Subject Rights
As Data Subject, you have the following rights, which can be exercised at any time with regard to Panini:
to request access to your Personal Data, (and/or a copy of such Personal Data), as well as further information on the current treatment of them;
to request the correction or updating of your Personal Data processed by Panini, where they are incomplete or out of date;
to request the deletion of your Personal Data from the Panini databases, where you deem the processing unnecessary or illegitimate;
to request the limitation of the processing of your Personal Data by Panini, where you believe that your Personal Information is not correct, necessary or is unlawfully processed, or if you had opposed its processing;
to exercise the right to data portability, i.e. to obtain a copy of the Personal Data supplied to Panini that relates to you in a structured format, for common use and readable by an automatic device, or to request transmission to another Data Controller;
to oppose the processing of your Personal Data, using a legal basis relating to your particular situation, which you believe should prevent Panini from processing your Personal Data;
to revoke (in the manner described later) your consent for marketing and profiling activities and for sending communications to third parties and to object to processing for soft spam purposes. The consent given for sending promotional communications consequent to processing for marketing and profiling purposes extends to communications sent using automated systems without an operator (e.g. e-mail), as well as to traditional contact methods, such as the postal service and the telephone. You can always revoke your consent to processing, even separately, e.g. by deciding to receive communications only by post and not via automated systems such as e-mail, or by blocking the use of third-party profiling cookies on Panini Websites to prevent the receipt of such communications;
to oppose the use of cookies when you use the Website: to this regard, please read the appropriate section of Panini's Cookie Policy.
Please note that the Personal Data you have provided to Panini can be modified:
If you are not a Privacy Minor, at any time via the Website section "Modify Data" (also accessible via the App) or by writing to the e-mail address:
webprivacy@panini.it
;
if you are a Privacy Minor, only your parent or guardian can do this at the time of registration on the Website and/or App. Panini specifies that the Minor may not modify his/her own Personal Data (e.g. the data on the registration form). Modification may be implemented only by a parent or legal guardian, by accessing the Panini Register of parents/legal guardians or by sending an e-mail to the address
webprivacy@panini.it
.
You can also stop receiving
Soft Spam
using the appropriate link at the bottom of each e-mail received (via the "Cancel" button).
For
Marketing
purposes, you can at anytime revoke your consent and ask to stop sending commercial information, by modifying your user profile preferences on the Website (also accessible via the App) or by writing to the e-mail address
webprivacy@panini.it
. In the case of communications received through IT tools, you can revoke your consent following the procedure indicated at the bottom of the communication (via the "Unsubscribe" button).
You can revoke your consent to processing for marketing purposes at any time and request that no further commercial information be sent, by modifying your profile preferences on the Website (also accessible via the App) or by writing to the e-mail address
webprivacy@panini.it
. In the case of communications received via e-mail, consent can be revoked by following the procedure indicated at the foot of such communications (via the "Cancel" button).
If you have an Android Device, go to "
Settings
", scroll to the bottom to "Notifications", use "
Show All
" or "Sent recently" to select the App and block notifications via "
Show/Consent Notifications
".
Consent for the purpose
Profiling
can be revoked by changing, at any time, the preferences of the user profile within the Website or by writing to the e-mail address
webprivacy@panini.it
.
If you are using the Website instead and intend to block processing arising from the use of third party profiling cookies, please read the appropriate section of Panini's Cookie Policy.
If the information provided by you is not sufficient to identify you unambiguously and / or with a sufficient degree of certainty, taking into account the specific type of right exercised (such as, in particular, those of access, copy and cancellation), Panini will request further information from you as required by specific regulatory provisions regarding the protection of personal data. In the event that Panini detects the absence or lack of suitable data to identify you and therefore there are reasonable doubts about your identity, Panini may then ask you to provide a copy of an identification document or any additional information deemed useful for your identification. In the event that you provide such a document, personal details such as your first and last name and your address should be clear in order to be able to identify you correctly, while any other information such as your photo or any other personal characteristics not necessary for identification should be removed or obscured before sending. We specify that our use of the information on your identity document is strictly limited to fully accounting for your request: in fact, such Data will be used only to verify your identity and will not be kept for longer than necessary for this purpose.
Panini also informs you that you always have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent Supervisory Authority (for example that of the State in which you have your habitual residence, in Italy the Guarantor for the Protection of Personal Data) if you believe that the processing of your data is contrary to the legislation in the field of personal data protection actually applicable.
