I- Amendments to the "Privacy Policy for parents or guardians of the users“
Panini S.p.A. has drawn up the following "
Privacy Policy
". With head office in Viale Emilio Po 380, 41126 Modena, Italy, Tel. +39 059 382111 - Fax +39 059 827431 (“
Panini
”) as Data Controller for the personal data collected in the Parents/Legal Guardians Register (“
Register
”) on
https://tutor.paninicloud.com/
(“Website”). You are required to register with the Register in order to grant under 18 years of age (e.g. your son/daughter, the child for whom you are the guardian), for whom you have parental responsibility so as he/she can access the sections of the websites and applications featuring our Adrenalyn XL™ products (hereinafter collectively referred as “Adrenalyn”) subject to regsitration. To clearly understand the purposes for which the data of under 18 years of age users (“Minor” or “Minors”) will be processed, please carefully read the entire Privacy Policy for Adrenalyn XL™ users, found at the foot of this page.
The Privacy Policy for Adrenalyn XL™ users found at the top of this page, as well as the text of the privacy policy for the specific Adrenalyn that the Minor intends to activate. These last texts are available in Section
H - Your Rights as Data Subject
found at the foot of this page.
This Privacy Policy is divided into sections (
"Sections"
and/or
"Section"
), each of which deals with a specific topic to allow you to read and search the topics quicker and more easily. The Website could contain links to other apps or websites. Panini is not liable for their privacy policies or for their relevant contents. Generally speaking, all personal data (
"Personal Data"
and/or
"Data"
) you provide to Panini or concerning the inclusion of your name into the Register, will be processed lawfully and in a transparent manner in accordance with the principles stated in the current legislation on the protection of personal data, such as transparency, fairness, lawfulness, data minimisation, purpose limitation, accuracy, storage limitation, integrity and confidentiality.
This Privacy Policy is written on the basis of the transparency principle using a simple and not too legal language to increase the level of understanding of the statements given.
A- Type of Personal Data Processed
Personal Data collected through the Application are listed below.
Name, Last name, Contact Details and other Personal Data
When you create an account on the website for the integration of your data in the Register (
https://tutor.paninicloud.com/
) Panini may ask your personal information such as: email, name, last name, gender, contact details, month and year of birth, degree of kinship with the child or dependent who has indicated you as parent or legal guardian of his and country of residence. In the same way, you may be asked to indicate other Data by using the Contact area on the Websites or Apps during the management of every relationship with Panini or by the data you decide to provide Panini via the Customer Service (also accessible by telephone).
Some sections of the Website and the nature of the communications you freely decide to send us via the electronic or physical addresses can include free text fields in which it is possible to provide Panini with information that may contain Personal Data. Being free fields, you may choose to communicate (even inadvertently) particular categories of Personal Data, such as those revealing political opinions, religious or philosophical beliefs, or union membership, as well as genetic data, biomedical data which can permit to uniquely identify a specific person, data related to health or sex life or sexual orientation.
Panini asks you not to disclose any of these types of data, unless you consider it strictly necessary to pursue the request you forward to us. Since the indication of such information is, as said, totally optional, if you choose to do so, Panini could process such data only with your explicit consent and in compliance with the current legislation. Panini, therefore, underlines the importance of expressing your explicit consent to the processing of these particular categories of Personal Data in case you decide to share them with Panini.
Personal Data of Third Parties
As mentioned in the previous paragraph, as the Website envisage empty text boxes in which it is possible to forward any type of message, these could in fact contain Personal Data relating also to other people. In all cases in which you decide to share such Data, you will be considered a self-appointed Data Controller and, as such, you will have to assume all the relevant legal obligations and responsibilities. Therefore, in this regard, you undertake to hold Panini harmless from any dispute, claim, request for compensation for damage from data treatment etc. that could reach Panini from people whose Personal Data have been forwarded by you in violation of the applicable rules on the protection of Personal Data.
As, in such cases, Panini does not collect this information directly from the data subjects (but indirectly from you), you guarantee that this specific treatment can be based on the consent of these data subjects or on another suitable lawful basis that legitimizes the processing of the information in question.
It nevertheless remains understood that, as regards the Data of the Minor that Panini asks you to modify, if necessary, and validate on the Register as his/her parent or guardian, the legal basis for processing the data is based on what legislation provides for on the topic of personal data protection. In fact, the latter states that the Data Controller (in this case Panini) must reasonably verify that the consent to processing, which requires the collection of that data, is actually granted or authorized by the holder of parental responsibility for the Minor (you in this case).
Data processed during interaction with social networks
You can register in the Register using your personal account on one of the social networks included on the registration form. In this case, the social network will automatically send Panini your Personal Data. You will only have to provide the additional Data required to complete your registration, as the social network will not pass this on to Panini. To know which Data the social network will share with Panini, please read the Privacy Policy provided by the social network you access and refer to the options for sharing Data indicated therein. Additionally, please note that in such cases Panini will provide specific privacy information, the latest version of which is always available
by clicking here
.
IP address spatial coordinates
When you create a profile on the Site or through the Application, we will collect the approximate spatial coordinates (state, city) of your IP address associated, only, with your last log-in. We will keep this information only to the extent strictly necessary and proportionate to ensure the purpose of Security, therefore for the sole purpose of obtaining information necessary to identify anomalies, fraudulent activities and/or abuse in the use and access to the Site and the Application.
Navigation Data and Cookies
The computer systems and software used to run the Website acquire, during their normal operation, some Personal Data whose transmission is implicit in the use of Internet communication protocols. This information is not collected by Panini to be associated with identified data subjects, but by its very nature could, through processing and association with data held by third parties, allow data subjects to be identified. This category of data includes the IP addresses or domain names of the computers used by the users connecting to the Website, the addresses in URI (Uniform Resource Identifier) notation of the requested services, the time of the request, the method used in submitting the request to the server, the size of the file obtained in response, the numerical code indicating the status of the response given by the server (good result, error, etc.) and other parameters related to the operating system and the user's computer.
These data are used for the sole purpose of obtaining anonymous statistical information on the use of the Website, to check its correct functioning and to identify anomalies and/or abuses. Except in cases where the data are used to ascertain responsibility in the event of hypothetical computer crimes against the Website or third parties, these data do not persist for more than seven days.
Information about the use of cookies is available in our Cookie Policy, which we kindly ask you to read by clicking on the “Manage cookies” button or the
and/or
(Manage Cookies)
both of which can be found in the Website footer.
B- Purposes of the Personal Data Processing
We will process your Personal Data for the following purposes:
to help if you forget the login/password for your personal account on the Register; allow operations strictly connected and contributory to the management of our relations with you, such as respond to queries received via the contact forms or by Panini (electronically and/or in printed form) at any of the addresses specified on the Website; to enable us to correctly fulfill our contractual obligations to you and vice versa; send you (when the protected Minor reaches the minimum age established by law for managing personal data independently and granting consent for processing linked to the supply of services by the information provider with full autonomy or the minimum age established by the law for accepting independently the Conditions of Use and other obligations of the service or services the Minor is accessing to) a communication to inform you about the above and about the deactivation and subsequent deletion of your profile, if there are no other Minors or Panini Services used by you that need that account
(Provision of Services)
;
to add your name to the Panini Register of Parents/Guardians; to allow you to give consent for the processing of the Data of the Minor for whom you have parental responsibility and/or accept the Condition of Use and other obligatoions, since these needed for registration with and access to the sections of the Adrenalyn websites or apps for which registration is required; to send you requests via e-mail to renew the optional consents needed to process the Data of the Minor for other purposes, e.g. if the Minor intends to use his/her Data to access versions of the Adrenalyn websites and apps for smartphones and tablets for which registration is required, that require additional processing with respect to previously-authorized versions of them (e.g. for participation in prize competitions); to enable Panini to use any available technology to verify that the consent has actually been given by you, as the holder of parental responsibility for the Minor, and perform checks on the truth of the information
(inclusion on the Register of Parents/Guardians and provision of consent on behalf of the Minor)
;
to obtain the information required to identify anomalies, illegal activity and/or abuse of the use of the Website towards Panini or third parties
(Security)
.
C- Personal Data Processing of Children below the Minimum Age established by law to grant consent to the Processing of Data
Children below the age of 16 or, under local laws, below the age established for consent-based processing of their Personal Data and, in all cases, under the age of 14 (as stated earlier, hereinafter "Privacy Minor" and/or "Privacy Minors") must obtain consent from a parent or guardian (you in this case) in order to register with the Adrenalyn websites and apps for smartphones and tablets for which registration is required, and access the sections reserved for registered users.
Since Panini is a company based in Italy, 14 is the minimum age for collecting consent for the processing of Personal Data to: provide services (e.g. register with the websites and apps for smartphones and tablets dedicated to the Adrenalyn ecosystem, and access the respective private sections). If, however, the local laws of the EU country in which the Privacy Minor resides establish a higher age threshold for giving consent for processing, the latter will prevail.
To understand clearly the purposes, please read carefully the entire Privacy Policy for the specific Adrenalyn that the Privacy Minor intends to activate.
These texts are available in
Section
"H- Data Subject Rights"
,
at the bottom of this page.
Please remember you need to register with the Register in order to manage access to the websites and apps for smartphones and tablets dedicated to the Adrenalyn ecosystem by your son/daughter or child for whom you are the guardian.
The Privacy Minor must complete the registration form on the websites and apps for smartphones and tablets dedicated to the Adrenalyn ecosystem to be activated, supplying all the Personal Data requested, including name, surname, family connection and e-mail address of a parent or legal guardian. The Privacy Minor will be asked to confirm the e-mail address provided on the registration form. Once this has been confirmed, your validation process will begin. Validation of the e-mail address provided by the Privacy Minor will not give him/her access to the sections of the Website and App subject to registration.
The registration request made by the Privacy Minor is suspended until it is managed directly by a parent or legal guardian. For this purpose, the parent or legal guardian (you in this case) must create a personal account on the Panini Register of parents/legal guardians by following the link in the e-mail received from the address
noreply@paninigroup.com
.
a. In case the parent or the legal guardian don't use the link within 72 hours from the reception or doesn't give consent to the processing of the personal data requested in the registration form, Privacy Minor will not able to access the sections of the websites and apps dedicated to the Adrenalyn they are activating under registration and the data collected in the registration form will be canceled in 24 hours.
After creating an account, the parent or guardian may examine and correct the Data sent by the Privacy Minor, as well as give and manage the consents required to process the Personal Data of the Privacy Minor needed to register with the websites and apps for smartphones and tablets dedicated to the specific Adrenalyn requested, and access their respective private sections (all being services supplied by the information provider). In order to take concrete steps to protect the Personal Data of Privacy Minors, Panini does not process any such Data for marketing or profiling purposes, or communicate it to third parties (as described at the top of this page in the privacy policy for the users of Adrenalyn XL™).
If the parent or guardian approves the registration request, the Privacy Minor can then access the websites and apps for smartphones and tablets dedicated to the Adrenalyn ecosystem at any time, without further notifications to the parent or guardian. The parent or guardian may also be notified about the consent requested to process the Data of the Privacy Minor needed for access to versions of the Websites and Apps dedicated to Adrenalyn Online that require additional processing with respect to previously-authorized versions of them (e.g. for participation in prize competitions).
The Privacy Minor will not be able to change the personal data included in the registration form and only the parent or legal guardian are allowed to do it by entering the Panini Parents/Legal Guardians Register or by contacting Panini at the address
webprivacy@panini.it
On the first day of the month in which the Privacy Minor reaches the age established by law for giving independent consent for the processing of his/her Personal Data, Panini will send a communication to the parent or guardian stating that, from the start of the month following receipt of the e-mail, the consents given by the parent or guardian on behalf of the Privacy Minor will no longer be valid and, from the first login to a Panini Service after that date, the last mentioned will be invited to give consent for the processing of his/her Personal Data for marketing and profiling purposes and (in relation to certain initiatives) for communication to third parties (which, as mentioned, Panini does not do in relation to Privacy Minors Data Subjects). An e-mail describing this procedure will also be sent to the Privacy Minor.
Accordingly, on reaching the minimum age envisaged by law, the Privacy Minor may give direct consent for the processing of his/her Personal Data, having become fully autonomous in the management of such Data and the related rights recognized in the applicable legislation, as well as in the expression of his/her preferences and consents. The parent or guardian will therefore cease to manage the Personal Data of the Privacy Minor.
Users minor of 18 are not allowed to purchase goods or services from our websites and apps for smartphones and tablet dedicated to Adrenalyn. To complete the registration process, under 18 years of age users also need the acceptance of the General Conditions of Use by the parent or guardian as described in the General Condition of Use the service.
D- Lawful Basis for Processing Personal Data, Mandatory/Discretionary Provision of Personal Data and Consequences in case of not providing
The lawful basis for processing the Personal Data, in accordance with the purposes set in the Section of this Privacy Policy (
B- Purposes of the Data Processing
), is as follows. The provision of Personal Data and the related processing for the purposes related to
Services Provision
, is strictly functional to the performance of the requested service and the correct execution of the contractual relationship with you and therefore they constitute a necessary condition for the establishment of the contractual relationship itself and the lawful basis of the processing. Consequently, failure to provide the Personal Data requested for this purpose, or the inaccuracy of the data provided, will make it impossible for Panini to carry out the service and the contractual relationship and would legitimize Panini to refuse to carry it out.
Panini requires Personal Data to be given for the relevant processing for the purposes of
Registration in the Register of parents/legal guardians
and
consent to be given on behalf of the Minor
in order to be able to comply with its legal obligations, which specifically envisage: (i) that consent on behalf of the Minor is given by the person with parental responsibility; (ii) to use the technology available to verify that in those cases, consent has been given by the person with parental responsibility for the Minor. Until the parent or legal guardian has given all the necessary Data to register on the Register and has given consent on behalf of the Minor, the latter will not be able to register on the websites and apps for smartphones and tablet dedicated to Adrenalyn.
The provision of Personal Data and its processing for
security
-related purposes is based on (i) the interest of Panini in identifying and preventing illegal conduct and determining liability in the event of IT offenses against the Website, Panini or third parties, that compromise the availability, authenticity, completeness, accuracy and confidentiality of the Personal Data retained or transmitted and, therefore on (ii) your interest in identifying and performing appropriate checks on any fraudulent accesses or illegal deeds carried out using the profile that you created on the Website.
E- Personal Data Sharing
The Personal Data will be made known to the Panini staff in charge of the development and management of the Register and Website that is authorized to process them for the purpose of achieving the aforementioned purposes and who are committed to confidentiality or otherwise have received an appropriate legal obligation to confidentiality.
Personal Data may be shared, used and transferred within the companies belonging to the Panini group for accounting and administrative purposes.
Personal Data will be made known to third parties, appointed as Data Processors, as they process Data on behalf of Panini (for example, companies responsible for managing and processing sales orders, suppliers with whom it is necessary to interact for the
Service Provision
such as hosting providers, platform providers for sending e-mails or, again, suppliers who perform technical maintenance activities including the maintenance of network equipment and electronic communications networks).
Personal Data may be shared with third parties with whom Panini has ongoing contractual relationships concerning services functional to the performance of the activity (such as audit firms, persons, companies or professional firms that provide assistance and advice on the subject, administrative, legal, tax, financial relating to the provision of the Services).
Finally, Personal Data will be communicated when requested to the competent taxation offices, or to other public bodies, according to the provisions of the laws in force.
Further information regarding the Data Processors is available by writing to Panini at the following e-mail address:
webprivacy@panini.it
Personal Data is not intended for publication or dissemination.
F- Personal Data Transfer
Given the international presence of Panini, some of your Personal Data may be shared with recipients, described in the previous section, located in countries that are not members of the European Economic Area. Such Data transfers will be the subject of adequate guarantees, including adequacy decisions and Standard Contract Clauses approved by the European Commission, in combination with the adoption of additional legal, technical and organizational measures or other guarantees intended to protect the Personal Data adequately, in accordance with the related European regulations.
More information is available by writing to Panini at the following address:
webprivacy@panini.it
G- Personal Data Retention
The Personal Data processed for the purpose of
Services Provision & Contractual Obligations
will be retained by Panini for the time strictly necessary for the execution of the requested service and for the correct execution of the contractual relationship with you. As this Personal Data is processed to provide you with the Services and allow the execution of the contractual relationship, Panini may keep them for a longer period, in particular for what may be necessary in order to protect the interests of Panini against possible claims arising from the
Services Provision
.
Panini also specifies that the authentication credentials for the Register will be valid for a period of 54 months from the Minor's last access to the websites and apps for smartphones and tablet dedicated to the sepcific activated Adrenalyn (the logic is based on the fact that the storage time of the Minor's credentials to access the websites and applications is 54 months), if at the end of that period the Minor is still underage. Otherwise, the authentication credentials will remain valid until the month after the Minor reaches 18 years of age. At the end of that period, the data will be made anonymous.
Your requests, and the data contained in them, collected via the Customer Service or Contact area on the website will be maintained for one year from the closure of the request in order to allow Panini to handle any additional requests received after closure. At the end of this period the Data that permit the identification, even indirect, of a physical person (such as name, surname, e-mail) will be made anonymous and maintained, only in the form of aggregated data, for statistical purposes.
Personal Data processed for inclusion on the Register of Parents/Guardians and to give consent on behalf of the Minor will be retained for up to 6 months from the date on which your child or ward reaches the 18 years of age. At the end of such period, any Data that enables identification (even indirectly) will be rendered anonymous and retained solely in aggregated form for statistical purposes.
On the first day of the month in which a child for whom you are the guardian reaches the age established by the law for autonomously giving consent to the processing of their Personal Data, Panini will send you a communication informing you that from the beginning of the month following receipt of the e-mail, the consent given by you on behalf of the child will no longer be valid and they will be invited to express consent to the processing of their Personal Data the next time they log in. An e-mail containing an indication of this procedure will also be sent to them.
Panini will store the Personal Data processed for the purpose of Security for the time strictly required for the aforementioned purpose and, therefore, until Panini is obliged to keep it to safeguard itself in court to give that Data to the competent authorities.
H- Data Subject Rights
At any time you are entitled, as Data subject, to:
request access to your Personal Data, (and/or a copy of such Personal Data), as well as further information on the current treatment of them;
request the correction or updating of your Personal Data processed by Panini, where they are incomplete or out of date;
request the deletion of your Personal Data from the Panini databases, where you deem the processing unnecessary or illegitimate;
request the limitation of the processing of your Personal Data by Panini, where you believe that your Personal Information is not correct, necessary or is unlawfully processed, or if you had opposed its processing;
exercise the right to data portability, i.e. to obtain a copy of the Personal Data supplied to Panini that relates to you in a structured format, for common use and readable by an automatic device, or to request transmission to another Data Controller;
oppose the processing of your Personal Data, using a legal basis relating to your particular situation, which you believe should prevent Panini from processing your Personal Data;
Please note that the Personal Data you provided to Panini may be changed at any time, by logging in to the Register with his/her own authentication credentials or by writing to:
webprivacy@panini.it
. You may exercise the above rights by means of the methods indicated above.
If the information provided by you is not sufficient to identify you unambiguously and / or with a sufficient degree of certainty, taking into account the specific type of right exercised (such as, in particular, those of access, copy and cancellation), Panini will request further information from you as required by specific regulatory provisions regarding the protection of personal data. In the event that Panini detects the absence or lack of suitable data to identify you and therefore there are reasonable doubts about your identity, Panini may then ask you to provide a copy of an identification document or any additional information deemed useful for your identification. In the event that you provide such a document, personal details such as your first and last name and your address should be clear in order to be able to identify you correctly, while any other information such as your photo or any other personal characteristics not necessary for identification should be removed or obscured before sending. We specify that our use of the information on your identity document is strictly limited to fully accounting for your request: in fact, such Data will be used only to verify your identity and will not be kept for longer than necessary for this purpose.
Panini also informs you that you always have the right to lodge a complaint with the competent Supervisory Authority (for example that of the State in which you have your habitual residence, in Italy the Guarantor for the Protection of Personal Data) if you believe that the processing of your data is contrary to the legislation in the field of personal data protection actually applicable.
Lastly, to understand clearly the purposes for which the Data of the Minor is processed, please read carefully the entire Privacy Policy for the specific Adrenalyn service that the Minor intends to activate.
